I had another seizure yesterday.
My doctor's have no CLUE what to do. 
It's not my blood sugar, a tumor, mono, B12 deficiency, high blood pressure, or my meds. We've tested it all. I'm on a low dose of anti-seizure medication and it IS NOT WORKING. I had another one while I was at work, as in WORKING WITH CHILDREN. Thank God none of them saw, because they were at art. 

I'm at a loss here.

I mean, where do I START?!?!?
Barack Obama is the next President of the United States of America. 
He's a Liberal, and he's BLACK (collective gasp), and his father was MUSLIM(another, deeper gasp).
AND.....

I could not be more proud of the USA. 

For everyone that is all "F&*K this, I'm moving to Canada!", let me be the first to say don't let the metaphoric door between this country and the next hit your sorry, ignorant ass on the way out.

PUT UP OR SHUT UP people. The time for change has come. Embrace the new government. Get on with your life. Obama is not going to legalize crack or knock out "Joe the Plumber" or rap the National Anthem or start a new war...so chill the eff out man. Just because he's black doesn't mean the world will end. 

It makes me sad to see so much hate in this world.

You know, it's true that I live in a small, southern, mostly white town in the Bible Belt of America, but it still doesn't make up for the sheer ignorance I see from time to time. Allow me to vent/rant on a few political issues::::

1) I voted last Wednesday. It was EXTREMELY busy, and yet, I saw MAYBE 2 young people (ie under, like 40) voting. Do we REALLY want some old farts to decide who runs our freaking country for the next 4 years!?!?! COME ON PEOPLE!!! Get WITH IT!  

2) At the elementary school I work at, I overheard one of my children saying "Obama will never win because he's black and someone will shoot him!"
True, this is coming from the mouth of a 9 year old, but honestly, WHERE THE HELL do you think he picked this up from?!!?!?! You know good and well his racist parents are at home putting those ideas in his head, and he is too impressionable to reason things out otherwise.

3) I enjoy a good debate, I really do. If you want to battle with me over politics or my beliefs on something, if it is APPROPRIATE, I will go! But how DARE someone tell me I'm WRONG for what I believe. I would NEVER personally attack someone because they share a different opinion than me. Those that know me know I am a  bleeding hearted hippie liberal, and GUESS WHAT????? I don't lose any sleep over the fact that the man I voted for doesn't share the same skin color or exactly the same religious views as me. So when someone comes at me and tells me I'm wrong, that I should rethink the lifestyle I'm living, well screw you buddy. I would never say such a thing to another person. But then again, that's just the hippie in me.

If you read all this, you rock. Comments, anyone???

HAPPY NEW YEAR!
Spent New Year's Eve with the fam and Court, just like last year. We'd been watching the Law and Order: SVU marathon all day....it's tradtion now :) 
We got BWW (veggie burger for me, I'm addicted to them) and I made Vegan Cookies for everyone (and surprisingly even daddy, king of sweets, ate them) and we watched "Lady in the Water", "Little Miss Sunshine", and "Accepted". We watched the ball drop and made about 50 Ryan Seacrest jokes lol
I hope this year turns out to be as good as the last. I cannot believe my baby sister graduates from high school in a few months....and I turn 20. I feel so old :(

I can't believe either how much has happened in 1 year.. I've changed so much. I've lost and gained some friends...gotten closer to some and drifted away from others. Things happened that would have never even crossed my mind 2 years ago.
I've finally learned to appreciate the little things at home I took for granted before. I love my small town, the boringness and hickishness of it. The way that I can go anywhere in Stedman and I run into people...hows ECU hows your mom your dad  has stacey graduated yet?...I love my animals and my accent (which has gotten SOOO much stronger since ive been here, ps) I love that we have 1 stop light and the biggest attraction in town is the Andys. I love my entire family and how they drive me crazy and yet I love them more than anything. I love my parents and what they sacrifice for us, and how they give me hope for love b/c they truly are soulmates. I love my sister and how she understands me more than anyone, and I don't have to say a word to her. I love that we beat the crap outta each other and still get along. We really are Chris and Mike from Just Friends... I love tennilley and how she gets me so well also. I love that things don't change so much here...everything is sort of gradual shifts. Stedman is full of constants. My room is always the same, my family, Tennille and Court are here, my animals, my house doesn't change....I think I need that.
Greenville is a different story. My life is crazy, constant change and utter chaos. I'm always on the go, never sleeping, eating cheap crappy food and taking the bus everywhere. No one knows me in Greenville...I feel so anonymous but I have a bigger base of friends....strange. I have Theatre which keeps me occupied...sometimes I feel like I can't slow down. I wouldn't change it though...
06 was a great year.

You know what? I'm madly in love with both of my lives.

get thee back to Greenville
2 days baby!

I'm feeling restless here.
I miss my wonderful roommates and my boys.
I'm ready to re-do my room, but I'm stuck. I want it to be mature, less dormish as Amy put it :), and reflect more of the serious side of me. I don't know, people don't see that side of me as much. The side that loves yoga and nature and being a vegetarrian and peace and candles and trying to be nice to my body. The side that is cultured and enjoys illectual deep conversations and walking and tofu and animals and meditating and the Indian culture. Wow I just made the most random list ever :)
i dunno.

Going into a big city always makes me feel so country-bumpkinesque. I feel so unexposed and in awe of the buildings and such...like a bad tourist.
We went to Raleigh today and had sooooo much fun. 
We went and looked at State for my sister, got some delish coffee, walked around downtown and Fayettville Street, ate lunch at a place Christina talks about called Lilly's Pizza (MOUTHGASM OMFG), and went shopping.
I got 5 new tops, some Nollie perfume, jewlery, stuff for my apartment and a funny calender.

I've decided to sorta re-do my room at the apartment.... a little more mature.  Right now my theme is "fire hazzard". 

Well, not really, but I have a crapload of candles...so. haha I went a little crazy at Pier 1 Imports do to a mega huge sale...whoopsie :) [[And not to worry, my avid and adoring readers, because Tinkerbell is "mature" in my eyes, so she will not be leaving anytime soon :D]]

It was a good day. Glad to be outta the freakin house..I thought I was gonna start shredding my eyelids soon. I'm ready to be back in Greenville...only 5 more days! Not that I don't love my family/house/room/town/ect....I just miss everybody in Gville terribly. I'm going to miss here when I leave too...it's a visious cycle.
 But first I need to see my Tennilley again and Miss Courtney Joelle....then I'll be content. I'd like to see Krystle before she leaves for IL, but I don't know if that's gonna happen :(
Anywho, that's all for now. I felt I should post a public entry as not to deny my stalkers that do not own an LJ account. hahaha I slay myself.

NOTHING went right today. I swear. 

I woke up late, almost missed the bus, waited for 45 mins for my friend who never showed up, hauled ass to the shop to find out I had to wait til after 1to do my project( even though Reid gave me permission to come @ 11...wtf?!?!), raced back home to get all my teaching shit together, then the printer fucked up and I ended up having to e-mail Patch all of my shit, took an imcomplete b.c I didn't have my hours, came back home long enough to pay my rent and then ran out the door again to help set up for the gala in the shop (I owed Reid like 30 mins), haul ass AGAIN to get there just to come in and find the place spotless, so Reid says we'll call it even and I can just go home. 

I got into the car and just started screaming and crying to try and make myself feel better, but it didn't work. I went and bought a pack of Cloves and smoked like 4 in a row I swear to God, but that made me feel worse.

When I got home I litterally fell into bed and didn't wake up til now. And thank God I did, because I still have 4 papers to write for tomorrow, plus my presentation. Oh and did I mention Blackboard keeps freezing and bootin me off...and all of my information I need to write the papers is on there?

Oh and everyone else in the house is all excited about Christmas now, and all of thier presents are wrapped and stockings are decorated, but I can't even take a break long enough to do that...oh wait. I haven't even got thier damn presents yet. AND I can't really afford it, ya know?

I'm going to have a breakdown.

God I am so ready for "dead week" (yeah right..more like "I'm about to drop dead week"!) to be over. I have like 94832094832904 projects due. I am SO stressed!
I finally finished my makeup project..yay!
Now I have to:<center>
write 4 papers
present a paper on GOD knows what
type my essay for Patch
final makeup project number 2
make up 30 mins time for Reid (basically...clean the shop)
take home test
build my flat
</center>
WHY WHY WHY DO I PROCRASTINATE?!?!
Oh and forgot to mention..I'm SUPPOSSED to be turning in my observation hours for Patch tomorrow...oh wait... I can't....because I ONLY HAVE 6 HOURS AND I'M SUPPOSSED TO HAVE 16!!!!!
So I'm going to have to take an incomplete and try and cram it in all exam week... 

[[Amy PLEASE let me know if you want to observe sometime :)]]

On a postive note, we may just be having a blowout party Wednesday night :) 
Dan's bringin like 4 people plus the boys upstairs will obviously be there, and Jared Shelby and Nadine are a given...I'm pretty stoked.
I REALLY need to just chill out and blow off some steam. Anyone who reads this is more than welcome to come...we're a hilarious group and I promise we'll entertain you :)

I'm going for my third all nighter in a row. Dear Lord, start the coffee.

I NEED ROOMMATES FOR NEXT YEAR!

i know it's soon to be thinking about this...but I have to decide whether or not to renew my lease. I kinda like P. Cove but I'm all for moving if I can live with someone I freakin know. I don't want to live with complete strangers!!

Come on guys. I bathe. I don't party too much, but I don't mind if you do. I know how to clean....and I'm  not even home that much cuz Theatre owns my soul.

Any takers? I'm totally serious...:)


On another note...Alisha's birthday was today. I baked her a cute little cake and got her a little Apple bath set. Then me her and Em went out to Mi Cabanas. I made a video thingy....

I know what everything means now. The hospital visit, the shaking, the convulsing, the speech problems the disorentiation...
 <center> I'm diabetic.</center>
I still feel like I'm in shock. I laid in my bed for hours today, staring at the celing, just letting the tears come and the reality sink in. This has changed my whole life, and to be honest: I'm scared.
I'm scared of what this all means.

Today was a good day. It was so so so nice outside. 

We opened all the windows and the balcony door and lit fall scented candles and baked Pumpkin cookies and listened to Cartel and Jack Johnson.

I love my little apartment and my roommates :)

Tomorrow Stace is coming up and me her and Em are going to see Cartel at the Lincoln. I'm excited.
Plus Amber is coming down from App...I miss her so much!

On another note, today was good, but I don't feel satisfied. I just don't like Greenville. I want to be somewhere with more scenery than a McDonalds on every corner. I want to be in the mountains or at the beach. 

I'm sorta considering transferring to App. Boone is so close to the mountians that I love so much. But at the same time, I love ECU the school, and that's what I'm really here for.
I don't know. Emily made a good point when she said that since Stace is 99.9999% sure she's going there, I can just visit.

Eh. I just don't know anymore.

Sooooo this weekend was uh-mazing. Friday::: Sonic & Christina's with Jez, THE Moses (haha, I felt the need to capitalize), and Ashley to make some loverly candy and pies and such. Yum. Watched Narnia. Drove home and crashed Saturday:: Literally slept til 3. Woke up, had dinner with Christina around 6, and then Coldstone <3 Went and got her car from the towing place...again. Good ole G Vegas Towes again... Then, once again crashed Sunday:: Spontanous road trip to Atlantic Beach with 2/3 of my roomies. We had an AMZING time....riding down the freeway with the sunroof open singing along to Brittney Spears and Maroon 5 and flirting with the cars that drove past (and of course....throwin up the SHOCKER!!! hahaha) Overall...fab weekend.
